history of the Spanish Empire. This volume delves into the early, seemingly anecdotal stories of the war to map the great variety and interconnection of the narratives. It asks such questions as how did the Jesuits write about the Revolt, what can we find in Italian chronicles and how did the war look from the perspective of a local nobleman or a Spanish commander?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aRevolutionszBenelux countries. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Western.2bisacsh  aCultural history of warfare.  aDutch Revolt.  aEarly modern history of Europe.  aEarly modern warfare.  aEighty Years’ War.  aEpisodic narratives.  aHabsburg Low Countries.  aPhilip II.  aSpanish tercios.  aWar narratives.1 aBelmonte, Beatriz Santiago, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEsser, Raingard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFagel, Raymond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFagel, Raymond, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFrancés, Leonor Álvarez, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHanlon, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLavenia, Vincenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMartínez, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMoerman, Dániel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aReijner, Cees, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRodríguez Salgado, M.J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSantiago Belmonte, Beatriz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aThomas, Werner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 avan de